He primarily is remembered today for "Heliotrope Bouquet", the rag in which he shares compositional credit with Scott Joplin: The nature of the music seems to indicate that Chauvin provided the basis for the first two strains, and Joplin wrote the last two and edited the work into a cohesive piece due to the debilitating effects of Chauvin's illness.
